sql:
SELECT psnr, ssim, mse, dc
FROM quality_assessments
WHERE psnr > 30 AND ssim > 0.8;

SELECT DISTINCT u.user_name
FROM users u
INNER JOIN images i ON u.user_id = i.created_by;

external_knowledge:
- "artistic harmony with the cosmic quartet" refers to the condition where the last three digits of an image resolution, interpreted as an integer, are divisible by 4;
- "dimensions of these creations" refers to the resolution of the image;
- "masterpieces" refers to images uploaded to the database;
- "artists" refer to the users who uploaded the images.

- Guardians of the data realm: refers to users with the role 'admin';
- Shine brighter than the average shadow: means the mean value of the features is greater than 0.5;
- Looking over: signifies that the admin is either the creator of the image or has extracted the features from the image.

sql:
SELECT i.image_name, i.image_type, i.image_format
FROM images i
JOIN quality_assessments qa ON i.image_id = qa.image_id
WHERE qa.psnr = (
    SELECT MAX(psnr) FROM quality_assessments
);
